[src:operational-amplifiers/op-amp] can be a critical issue for high-frequency operation, where it reduces input impedance and may cause phase shifts.
[src:operational-amplifiers/op-amp] When high resistances or sources with high output impedances are used in the circuit, these small currents can produce significant voltage drops.
